reviews.headline: Covers imperfections
reviews.comments: I love add this foundation covers completely all my medium colored spots from sun damage. It is a matte formula, but yet leaves your skin looking fresh and not dry . Very easy application with a brush which is what I used to apply my makeup.

reviews.headline: Great foundation
reviews.comments: I hav been using It foundation for over 10 years and I love how it looks so natural.  I get compliments on my skin.  Very good coverage of darker spots and blemishes.

reviews.headline: Not for me

reviews.headline: This is perfect for a steamy summer
reviews.comments: I have been using the regular IT Cosmetics for several years and I love it.  But because of menopause, I have been really sweaty a shiny this summer, so when I saw this matte version last time I went to refill I thought I would try it.  It's perfect.   I'll see how winter does for me, I may have to switch back to the regular version,  Both feel the same, which is why i love them, this when just hides the shine.

I received this product as a promotional gift for my honest review and feedback. 
I have been a fan of IT cosmetics for quite some time but I hadn't used their foundations prior to receiving this product. I am 39 years old with combination skin. Mostly oily in the T-zone. I have been using this product for over a week now and I can say that it can keep up with my busy sweaty days of running around after two toddlers. 
Pros:
Love all the awesome benefits of a CC cream, anti aging properties. 
Stays on well for over 8 hrs. 
Has a very decent SPF. Always wear SPF even if you don't go outside, all light will wreck your skin.
Helps control my oily skin. 

Cons: can't think of any really.
faceoff_positive.headline: New favorite foundation

faceoff_negative.comments: I've been buying (at Sephora) and using the original "oil free, matte" formula for the last 12 years or so - because it was absolutely amazing for my combo-oily skin and it had mineral SPF, which doesn't break me out (many other foundations and CC/BB creams do). The company has now re-formulated the product to be less matte and it is now "natural" but not oil free. The new formula feels a lot heavier and it accentuates the pores instead of smoothing them. It looks cakey and settles into lines. It transfers onto clothes easily. It also now has chemical SPF which is far worse for skin than mineral one. Why a company as great as IT Cosmetics would take their absolute best product (probably best-selling too) and turn it into useless gunk is beyond me. They just lost a long-time, loyal customer. I am now searching for another non-comedogenic CC cream that will be usable for my combo-oily skin. That's what happens when you try to rip off your loyal customers by switching from the more expensive mineral SPF to cheap chemical SPF. I am not going to purchase any of your products ever again until you bring back the old formula of this CC cream. And please don't reply with your "We're Sorry" cliche business lines. It does NOTHING for the customer - unless you give me the date when the old formula is coming back. Bye bye Not-It Cosmetics.
faceoff_negative.headline: Unacceptable New Formula
